@node "FunTris" "1.  What is FunTris?"
FunTris is a multiplayer-tetris. 2-4 players can play at the same time.
(There is also one player game in FunTris, but it's quite boring to play
alone.)

I'm already done one tetris-clone (@{"ZapTris" link "ZapTris" 0}) and first I tried to make "Two
players game"-option on it. But it was pretty hard, because ZapTris is
already really big program and it was originally made for only one player.

That's why I decided to make FunTris. It's much more easier to make totally
new multiplayer-tetris-game than change ZapTris for 2 players.
@endnode

@node "Distributing" "2.1.  Distributing this game"
You can freely distribute _unregistered_ version of this game as long as all
@{"files" link "Files" 0} are in archive in their original form.
@endnode

@node "Files" "2.2.  Files in archive"
@{u}You should find these files from FunTris-archive:@{uu}


 @{b}FunTris@{ub}        - Executable main file

 @{b}Settings.Data@{ub}  - Latest settings
 @{b}Players.Data@{ub}   - Players and statistics

 @{b}FunTris.Guide@{ub}  - This guide-file
 @{b}FunTris.Text@{ub}   - Same texts in normal text-format

 @{b}RegForm.Text@{ub}   - Register-form (Just print&fill&send this, soon you are
                  playing your own registered FunTris)


"@{b}Settings.Data@{ub}"- and "@{b}Players.Data@{ub}"-files are automatically loaded when you
start game and saved when needed. If these files are missing, FunTris can
create new ones.


If you have registered this game, you also have file named "@{b}FunTris.Key@{ub}".
That is you personal registeration-key-file and it is *illegal* to copy that
file to anyone, distribute it in any form or modify it! Key-file is only for
you.
@endnode

