@node "Register" "3.2.  How to register"
@{u}Registeration is very simple operation:@{uu}

1. Print file named "@{b}RegForm.Text@{ub}" and fill it. Or if you don't have a
   printer, just write in any paper that you want to register FunTris, tell
   which version you have and your own name and address (+country). And, of
   course, all bugreports and suggestions are very welcome.

2. Put that paper and a registeration fee ($10 USD or 40 FIM) to envelope.
   (Only cash please. It's just an easiest way. And no coins. Those cannot
   be exchanged and those may broke the envelope.) Then just send it to
   me (@{"author" link "Author" 0}).

   (NOTE! If you have already registered @{"ZapTris" link "ZapTris" 0}, a registeration fee of
   FunTris is only $5 USD or 20 FIM (which isn't much more than disk&
   packing&posting). See "@{b}RegForm.Text@{ub}"-file.)

And that's it!


@{u}As soon as possible I'll send to you:@{uu}

1. Newest version of FunTris.

2. Your personal "FunTris.Key"-file, which makes your FunTris registered.
   (No more "Unregistered version delay" when you start playing FunTris and
   no more 5 minutes timelimit in game.)

3. Other shareware-/freeware-products I have made. (ZapTris, Mine!, Mato,
   AmiSplit, AmiFind, FileModifier....)

If you want, I can also send your key-file to you via UUENCODED E-Mail. It's
much more faster.


@{u}After you have become registered user:@{uu}

1. When you want new version of FunTris just get new unregistered version
   somewhere ("http://www.cs.helsinki.fi/~palaakso/" is good place to start)
   Unpack new archive and add your registeration-key-file ("@{b}FunTris.Key@{ub}") to
   your new FunTris-directory. After that you have new registered version of
   FunTris.

2. If you have any problems or good ideas, feel free to tell me about
   those. That's the way you can help me to make FunTris even better.
@endnode

