@node "CompuPlayers" "5.1.  Computer players"
@{u}Enabling computer players@{uu}

- Change player to "Anonymous (or CPU)"

- Change controlling method to "Computer"


@{u}Changing computer players speed and AI@{uu}

- Select controls and press <@{b}Enter@{ub}>

  - Use <@{b}Arrows@{ub}> to change thinking speed and artificial intelligence

  - Press <@{b}Enter@{ub}> to accept and <@{b}Esc@{ub}> to cancel

- Select sensitivity and use <@{b}Arrows@{ub}> to change shape moving speed


Note! When you make computer to think faster or smarter, it will use more
CPU-power. So, if you want to play against three superfast and extra-
intelligent computer opponent, you also need fast Amiga! Otherwise game
might get sticky.
@endnode

@node "Game Types" "5.2.  Different game types"
@{u}There are two different game types in FunTris:@{uu}

A)  @{b}All player are playing their own game.@{ub} Whatever yuor opponents are
    doing, it doesn't change your game. Winner is player with highest
    score. (Whey playing with this game type, you can make game
    timelimited.)

B)  @{b}Full lines go to opponents.@{ub} When you remove at least @{b}X@{ub} lines at once,
    those lines will be transfered to your opponents game area. (You can
    choose @{b}X@{ub} between 1-4. If you select 1, all lines you remove go to your
    opponents, so game won't take very much time...) Winner is the last
    player.
@endnode

@node "Scoring" "5.3.  Scoring"
- Every shape gives you a point.

- When you remove lines you get points as follows:

  1 line :  10 points
  2 lines:  30 points
  3 lines:  70 points
  4 lines: 150 points

  In other words try to remove as many lines as possible at a time to get
  better score.
@endnode

@node "Keys" "5.4.  Keys"
@{u}Main menu:@{uu}

              <@{b}ArrowUp@{ub}>,<@{b}ArrowDown@{ub}>,<@{b}Joy2-Up@{ub}>,<@{b}Joy2-Down@{ub}> - Move in menu

<@{b}ArLeft@{ub}>,<@{b}ArRight@{ub}>,<@{b}Enter@{ub}>,<@{b}J2-Left@{ub}>,<@{b}J2-Right@{ub}>,<@{b}J2-Fire@{ub}> - Make selections

      <@{b}Space@{ub}> - Start game

<@{b}Shift@{ub}>+<@{b}Esc@{ub}> - Save current settings and players and then quit (without
                any questions)


@{u}Game:@{uu}

 <@{b}Esc@{ub}> or <@{b}P@{ub}> - Pause game

 <@{b}Del@{ub}> or <@{b}M@{ub}> - Turn music on/off (if loaded)

<@{b}Help@{ub}> or <@{b}B@{ub}> - Hide/Show background picture (if loaded)

<@{b}Shift@{ub}>+<@{b}Esc@{ub}> - Stop playing and return to main menu

You can use <@{b}P@{ub}>, <@{b}M@{ub}> and <@{b}B@{ub}> keys only if any player isn't using those keys
as a control-key.


@{u}Always:@{uu}

<@{b}RightAmiga@{ub}>+<@{b}F@{ub}> - Swap between Workbench and FunTris

   <@{b}Control@{ub}>+<@{b}C@{ub}> - Quit game immediately (Settings and players will be not
                   saved) Normally you don't need to use this
@endnode

@node "Faster&Memory" "6.  How to make game faster and save memory"
@{u}If game is too slow, try these:@{uu}

- Decrease number of players

- Don't use background picture

- Play with joystick instead of keyboard; Keyboard-input is getting quite
  busy if there is four players tapping a keyboard at the same time

- Make computer-players to think slower

- Make computer-players less intelligence

- Don't use shape mirroring when playing with computer opponents
  (Shape mirroring slow down computer-players thinking)


@{u}If memory is getting low:@{uu}

- Don't use background picture

- Don't use background music
@endnode

